snippet.textDisplay: Good for Jimmy Johnson. He was successful with 2 Super Bowls in such a short time as Dallas Head Coach. He had plenty of talented superstar players that he guided to those 2 championships. The ONLY knock I have on the Pro Football HOF is that the requirements to get in are getting less and less. Ex: Bill Cowher was accepted in but he only has one Super Bowl in 2 appearances. He turned the Pittsburgh franchise back around from those last 7-8 years of less than spectacular Chuck Knoll years in the early to late 1980's. He is borderline entry in my humble opinion but as a Steeler fan I am happy for him. There are several members presently that I don't think they should be in but who am I?
